231
00:16:25,303 --> 00:16:26,938
{\an1}protect this village.

232
00:16:28,140 --> 00:16:29,574
We want to
change this land.

233
00:16:30,709 --> 00:16:33,845
{\an1}War will never leave this
land. That won't change.

234
00:16:34,613 --> 00:16:36,082
{\an1}Nothing will change.

235
00:16:37,216 --> 00:16:37,950
Yahiko...

236
00:16:40,354 --> 00:16:42,622
{\an1}Seems like little by little
things are changing.

237
00:16:48,296 --> 00:16:50,597
{\an1}All three of us are shinobi
who left our village because

238
00:16:50,631 --> 00:16:52,000
{\an1}we don't have too
much faith in

239
00:16:52,033 --> 00:16:53,635
{\an1}Hanzo's ways anymore.

240
00:16:54,469 --> 00:16:56,439
{\an1}But to tell you the truth,
we've all been getting

241
00:16:56,472 --> 00:16:58,773
{\an1}pretty sick of this
lifestyle, as well.

242
00:16:59,641 --> 00:17:01,744
{\an1}And when I looked into
your eyes earlier...

243
00:17:02,311 --> 00:17:04,414
{\an1}I began to feel like
starting over again.

244
00:17:05,815 --> 00:17:08,784
{\an1}But I don't feel like going
back to Hanzo is the answer.

245
00:17:09,519 --> 00:17:11,888
{\an1}So please, take us in
as your subordinates!

246
00:17:12,457 --> 00:17:13,190
No way!

247
00:17:13,558 --> 00:17:15,025
{\an1}What?! But before you--!

248
00:17:15,058 --> 00:17:18,029
{\an1}Not subordinates,
but as comrades.

249
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:24,403
{\an1}I'm Yahiko. And this is
Nagato and Konan.

250
00:17:25,871 --> 00:17:27,539
My name is
Kyusuke the Swift.

251
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:31,710
{\an1}If you need intel gathered,
just leave it to these legs.

252
00:17:32,479 --> 00:17:35,148
{\an1}Then go and seek out
other villages that are

253
00:17:35,181 --> 00:17:36,749
{\an1}suffering like this one.

254
00:17:43,656 --> 00:17:44,325
Yahiko...

255
00:17:44,959 --> 00:17:45,626
What?

256
00:17:46,227 --> 00:17:47,661
You should name
our group.

257
00:17:49,930 --> 00:17:52,601
{\an1}There are more of us.
It'll be necessary soon.

258
00:17:55,704 --> 00:17:56,539
A name, huh?

259
00:18:02,078 --> 00:18:04,046
{\an1}How about The Akatsuki?

260
00:18:05,149 --> 00:18:08,018
{\an1}This nation weeps because
of the suffering of war.

261
00:18:09,119 --> 00:18:10,687
{\an1}So we will change
this nation--

262
00:18:11,523 --> 00:18:12,823
{\an1}No, the whole world.

263
00:18:13,358 --> 00:18:15,360
{\an1}And we shall usher
in a new dawn!

264
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:16,995
Akatsuki...

265
00:18:17,962 --> 00:18:18,997
{\an1}That's a great name.

266
00:18:19,898 --> 00:18:22,434
Akatsuki. Great,
then it's decided!

267
00:18:22,734 --> 00:18:23,435
Yeah!

268
00:18:37,851 --> 00:18:40,221
{\an1}I can't believe how much the
Akatsuki's suddenly grown.

269
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:41,455
Incredible.

270
00:18:42,557 --> 00:18:44,825
{\an1}They've all come to believe
in your dream. Although

271
00:18:44,859 --> 00:18:47,795
{\an1}perhaps more than anything,
they're tired of war.

272
00:18:49,764 --> 00:18:52,569
{\an1}If everyone unites, we
can achieve peace.

273
00:18:54,571 --> 00:18:56,071
Say, where's
Konan right now?

274
00:18:56,606 --> 00:18:58,541
She went out a
little while ago.

275
00:18:58,575 --> 00:18:59,742
Why's that?

276
00:19:00,043 --> 00:19:00,944
{\an1}["I dunno" grunt]

277
00:19:04,515 --> 00:19:05,182
This is...

278
00:19:05,916 --> 00:19:07,051
It's Konan's.

279
00:19:09,853 --> 00:19:11,656
{\an1}It says, "My dear Konan..."

280
00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:15,093
{\an1}"From the first moment
I laid eyes on you..."

281
00:19:15,527 --> 00:19:16,394
Is this--?!

282
00:19:17,062 --> 00:19:18,330
{\an1}It's a love letter.

283
00:19:19,097 --> 00:19:22,168
{\an1}"I've wanted to ask you how
you feel about me. I'll be

284
00:19:22,201 --> 00:19:24,604
{\an1}waiting anxiously on the
back terrace for you."

285
00:19:25,538 --> 00:19:26,540
"Kyusuke."

286
00:19:27,474 --> 00:19:30,244
Don't tell me...
Konan's gone there?!

287
00:19:30,277 --> 00:19:31,078
I dunno...

288
00:19:37,017 --> 00:19:38,253
[chuckle]

289
00:19:38,286 --> 00:19:40,822
{\an1}Yahiko, didn't you
have something to do?

290
00:19:40,855 --> 00:19:42,725
Huh?! Oh, yeah,
that's right!

291
00:19:42,757 --> 00:19:45,793
{\an1}Almost forgot! I need to go
to the bathroom! [laughter]

292
00:19:45,827 --> 00:19:47,096
{\an1}I'm gonna wet myself!

293
00:19:55,871 --> 00:19:56,805
That guy!

294
00:19:57,507 --> 00:20:00,076
{\an1}Guess running isn't
all he's fast at!

295
00:20:00,910 --> 00:20:03,447
{\an1}Well when we get more
comrades, it seems we get

296
00:20:03,481 --> 00:20:05,549
more competition
in love, too!

297
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:07,385
{\an1}Yeah, no kidding...

298
00:20:08,286 --> 00:20:09,787
Oh, Nagato!

299
00:20:10,054 --> 00:20:11,922
Do you like
Konan, Yahiko?

300
00:20:13,659 --> 00:20:15,662
Dummy! It's
nothing like that!

301
00:20:16,928 --> 00:20:19,432
{\an1}Well, you know, I
think Konan likes you.

302
00:20:19,898 --> 00:20:20,799
Huh?!

303
00:20:23,903 --> 00:20:24,837
{\an1}Oh, he's leaving.

304
00:20:26,473 --> 00:20:27,741
{\an1}I know you're there...

305
00:20:28,409 --> 00:20:30,277
Yahiko, Nagato.

306
00:20:31,746 --> 00:20:33,947
Konan, what did
you tell that guy?

307
00:20:35,115 --> 00:20:37,851
{\an1}I said I don't have time
for a relationship till

308
00:20:37,885 --> 00:20:39,854
{\an1}we make the Akatsuki's
dream come true.

309
00:20:40,723 --> 00:20:41,624
{\an1}Isn't that right?

310
00:20:43,058 --> 00:20:44,025
Konan...

311
00:20:44,727 --> 00:20:45,695
Yahiko!

312
00:20:46,462 --> 00:20:48,698
{\an1}Can you help me out
with some training?

313
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,168
This jutsu...

314
00:20:52,201 --> 00:20:53,869
{\an1}...doesn't work in the rain!

315
00:21:05,049 --> 00:21:06,384
{\an1}Oiled paper, huh?

316
00:21:07,553 --> 00:21:08,487
Great idea.

317
00:21:09,053 --> 00:21:10,422
I experimented.

318
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:13,492
If you hesitate,
I'll leave you behind!

319
00:21:14,293 --> 00:21:15,562
{\an1}Like I'd let you!

320
00:22:57,107 --> 00:22:59,211
{\an1}<i>Hanzo is setting an example</i>
<i>for the rest of us shinobi</i>

321
00:22:59,244 --> 00:23:02,047
{\an1}<i>by fighting to try to bring</i>
<i>peace to this world.</i>

322
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:05,116
{\an1}<i>We will prove that one day</i>
<i>the Akatsuki will surpass</i>

323
00:23:05,150 --> 00:23:06,419
{\an1}<i>him in that quest!</i>

324
00:23:06,452 --> 00:23:08,554
{\an1}<i>I approve of a group that</i>
<i>resolves issues through</i>

325
00:23:08,588 --> 00:23:10,924
{\an1}<i>nonviolent means. It</i>
<i>will help me realize</i>

326
00:23:10,958 --> 00:23:13,827
{\an1}<i>my dream of uniting the</i>
<i>Five Nations without force.</i>

327
00:23:14,695 --> 00:23:18,398
{\an1}<i>Next time on Naruto</i>
<i>Shippuden: "Creeping Shadow."</i>

328
00:23:19,199 --> 00:23:21,736
{\an1}<i>So they're the apprentices</i>
<i>of that brat! [chuckle]</i>

